cz.hobrasoft.pdfmu.error

Enum ErrorType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ErrorType>
      • cz.hobrasoft.pdfmu.error.ErrorType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ErrorType>

    public enum ErrorType
extends Enum<ErrorType>
    Contains all the types of errors (failing conditions) that can happen in PDFMU. Every error type has a code and a message template associated. The codes are loaded from the resource "cz/hobrasoft/pdfmu/error/ErrorCodes.properties" and the messages are loaded from the resource bundle "cz.hobrasoft.pdfmu.error.ErrorMessages". The keys in both of the resource files must match the strings returned by Enum.toString() (which returns the enum constant name by default).

    Assertions are in place that ensure that every error type has a code and a message associated, and that the codes are unique. If assertions are disabled and a resource is missing or incompatible, default values are provided.

    How to add a new error type:

    • Add an enum constant in ErrorType
    • Add a corresponding code in ErrorCodes.properties
    • Add a corresponding message in ErrorMessages.properties
    Author:
    Filip Bartek

      • getCode

        public int getCode()
        Returns the error code associated with this error type. The code should uniquely identify the error. The value of DEFAULT_ERROR_CODE is returned if no code is associated with this error type. The error codes are loaded from the resource "cz/hobrasoft/pdfmu/error/ErrorCodes.properties" when the first ErrorType is instantiated.
        Returns:
        the error code associated with this error type, or -1 if none is associated

      • getMessagePattern

        public String getMessagePattern()
        Returns the message pattern associated with this error type. The message patterns are loaded from the resource bundle "cz.hobrasoft.pdfmu.error.ErrorMessages" when the first ErrorType is instantiated.
        Returns:
        the message pattern associated with this error type, or null if none is associated
